Date: Thu 21 Jul 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(29) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=20514


Lumpy skin disease, Montenegro
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 21 Jul 2016 from Dr Vesna Dakovic, Acting Director, Administration for Food Safety, Veterinary and Phitosanitary Affairs, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Podgorica, Montenegro

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 Jul 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 21 Jul 2016
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease [LSD] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Gusinje, Gusinje, Plav
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3 / 1 / - / 1 / -

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 33.33 / **/ ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive; related to outbreaks of lumpy skin disease in other Balkan countries.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestations; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; official destruction of animal products; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; modified stamping out; control of vectors; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Podgorica Diagnostic Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Cattle / real-time PCR / 21 Jul 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The spread of the LSD virus to the cattle population of Montenegro is not surprising, given reports of its circulation in neighboring countries. See comments by Mod.AS in ProMED- mail post 20160701.4321118.

For a general overview of the LSD situation in the area, please refer to the "disease outbreak maps" for the dates 1 May 2014 to 21 Jul 2016 at http://tinyurl.com/jtkgs6t.

Map of Montenegro is available at, http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/montenegro-political-map.htm. - Mod CRD]
